/Restricting 🐌 Ui design liberties/

(Hand drawn Diagram)

|> Info
    When implementing a theme library at projectTogether in 2021//22, I had a conversation with the designer 
    about making Ui design less micromanagement and more declarative. In short, he didn't like it.
    So here is a library that aims to make designers redundant.

|> List
    -- I can define layout regions and then use them to write views in nested modules that appear
        in several regions at once.
    -- The complete Ui state is serialised to the URL so that when I share a link, the recipient
        will see what I see.
    -- For parts of the model that are editable, the library can auto-generate appropriate
        user controls so that Ui design and data model are guaranteed to stay isomorphic.

